Sentencas: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells (MS-SOFC) with infiltrated catalysts on both anode and cathode side are operated in direct-flame configuration, with a propane flame impinging on the anode.
Titulo: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operated in direct-flame configuration

Sentencas: Placing thermal insulation on the cathode dramatically increases cell temperature and performance.
Titulo: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operated in direct-flame configuration

Sentencas: The optimum burner-to-cell gap height is a strong function of flame conditions.
Titulo: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operated in direct-flame configuration

Sentencas: Cell performance at the optimum gap is determined within the region of stable non-coking conditions, with equivalence ratio from 1 to 1.9 and flow velocity from 100 to 300 cm s(-1).
Titulo: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operated in direct-flame configuration

Sentencas: In this region, performance is most strongly correlated to flow velocity and open circuit voltage.
Titulo: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operated in direct-flame configuration

Sentencas: The highest peak power density achieved is 633 mW cm(-2) at 833 degrees C, for equivalence ratio of 1.8 and flow velocity of 300 cm s(-1).
Titulo: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operated in direct-flame configuration

Sentencas: The cell starts to produce power within 10 s of being placed in the flame, and displays stable performance over 10 extremely rapid thermal cycles.
Titulo: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operated in direct-flame configuration

Sentencas: The cell provides stable performance for > 20 h of semi-continuous operation.
Titulo: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operated in direct-flame configuration
